raceComments: {"comment":"11. FIELDELO was stakes-placed as a 3-year-old and will be even stronger this season. She won the latest of her 2 jumpouts, and is unbeaten fresh up in her light career. She handles any type of track condition and is sure to be among the hardest to beat here. 1. SHIRSHOV is a very handy sprinter with a good record on this track. He was runner-up here 4 weeks ago and will be peaking third up. The blinkers are on for the first time, and he is poised to go one better. 3. POWER OF THE BRAVE resumed at an easier level at Hawkesbury 17 days ago and was too strong late for his rivals, scoring by more than a length. He has 3.5kg less to carry this time, and from a handy gate, he should be right in the thick of the finish again. 10. ONE HARD LADY is a very promising mare who has a few tricks to go along with her talent. She had to trial again after winning here fresh up by a nose, and on raw ability, she has the scope to race right through the grades this season. Stick with her.","runners":[11,1,3,10],"exclusive":true}
